SIMPLE: eternal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eternal
<hw>E*ter"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧ternel</ets>, L. <ets>aeternalis</ets>, fr.
<ets>aeternus</ets>. See <er>Etern</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Without
beginning or end of existence; always existing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>eternal</qex> God is thy refuge.</q> <rj><qau>Deut.
xxxiii. 27.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To know wether there were any real being, whose duration has been
<qex>eternal</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without end of existence or duration; everlasting;
endless; immortal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That they may also obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus,
with <qex>eternal</qex> glory.</q> <rj><qau>2 Tim. ii.
10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Continued without intermission; perpetual;
ceaseless; constant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And fires <qex>eternal</qex> in thy temple shine.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Existing at all times without change;
immutable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hobbes believed the <qex>eternal</qex> truths which he
opposed.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What are the <qex>eternal</qex> objects of poetry among all
nations, and at all times?</q> <rj><qau>M. Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Exceedingly great or bad; -- used as a strong
intensive.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Some <xex>eternal</xex> villain.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The Eternal City</b></col>, <cd>an appellation of
Rome.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Everlasting; endless; infinite; ceaseless;
perpetual; interminable. See <er>Everlasting</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eternal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eternal
<hw>E*ter"nal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of the
appellations of God.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Law whereby the <qex>Eternal</qex> himself doth work.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is endless and immortal.</def>
<rj><au>Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eternalist</ent>⟦br⟧
